How is everyone holding up? This has been a pretty intense week.

One thing I did yesterday that felt really good -- I sent a handful of emails to old co-workers and friends to just checkin and say I was thinking about them. Everyone responded almost immediately. It felt great to commiserate together a bit. A small lift in a rather grim week :slightly_smiling_face:

How are you managing? What has given you a lift this week?

text:
I’ve found it helpful to consciously focus my news intake around people/articles that are properly worried but also solution oriented.

It can be easy to read scary and negative headlines all day, but there are so many smart and motivating people working hard to solve problems and improve our spirits.

And there’s always dog videos <https://twitter.com/ladyhaja/status/1239666632793997315?s=20>
